annotationA: Ubiquitin-like domain-containing C-terminal domain phosphatase 1 is a nuclear HAD family phospho-Ser/Thr phosphatase that binds and dephosphorylates the nuclear 26S proteasome and inhibits proteasome activity
annotationB: 26S proteasome regulatory complex subunit p50; ATP binding; endopeptidase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: proteolysis; cellular process; protein catabolic process; proteasome-mediated ubiquitin-dependent protein catabolic process; Belongs to the AAA ATPase family
